Measures of Risk Aversion 

  absolute risk aversion: 
rA(x) = -u′′(x)/u′(x) 
  constant absolute risk aversion (CARA) 
u(x) =-e-αx 
  If x ~ N(μ,σ²),  CE(F) = μ - ασ²/2 
  relative risk aversion: 
rR(x) = -xu′′(x)/u′(x) 
  constant relative risk aversion (CRRA) 
u(x)=-x1-ρ/(1-ρ), 
  When ρ=1, u(x) = log(x). 

